-=-= English:
The finished program is intended for the Raspberry. IE. is a real "Windows version" meaningless.
Since I myself mainly work with CodeBlocks under Windows, there are also Windows options in the source.

For the Raspberry

gcc -s -O2 -Wall fake-hwclock.c -o fake-hwclock

fake-hwclock is in the /sbin directory. Rename the old script first. Then copy it.

cp fake-hwclock /sbin

That's it.
